# Page Plan: Course Catalog (Applications Landing)

## Route
`/applications`

## Purpose
A publicly accessible landing page that displays all available courses as a browsable catalog. Each course card has an "Enroll Now" CTA button that links to the course-specific application form at `/applications/[slug]`.

## Access
- **Fully public** — no authentication required.

## UI Layout

1. **Page Header**:
   - Title: "Available Programs" or "Our Courses"
   - Subtitle: brief institution tagline or enrollment window status (e.g., "Now accepting applications for Fall 2026")
   - If applications are currently closed (`isAcceptingApplications === false`), show an alert banner: "Applications are currently closed. Check back soon."

2. **Course Grid** (responsive: 1 col mobile, 2 col tablet, 3 col desktop):
   - Each course is a card showing:
     - Cover photo (or placeholder gradient)
     - Course name
     - Brief description (truncated to ~2 lines)
     - Duration badge (e.g., "12 Weeks")
     - Tuition fee (e.g., "₦250,000")
     - **"Enroll Now →"** CTA button → links to `/applications/[course.slug]`
   - If applications are closed, CTA is disabled with text "Applications Closed"

3. **Empty state** — "No courses available at this time." (when no active courses exist)

## Data Requirements
- `courses.listActive()` — fetches all courses where `isActive === true`, ordered by `order` field.
- `config.getSettings()` — checks if the application window is currently open.

## Navigation
- "Enroll Now" per card → `/applications/[slug]`

## SEO
- Title: "Apply Now — [Institution Name]"
- Meta description: "Browse available programs and start your enrollment today."
- Each course card should be wrapped in a semantic `<article>` element.
